.Dd June 2, 2026
.Dt MUSICD 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm musicd
.Nd music playback daemon
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar socket-path
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
runs the music playback daemon and listens for commands on the Unix-domain
socket at
.Ar socket-path .
It manages a queue of Matroska chapters and starts
.Xr play 1
for the active song.
.Pp
The queue is restored from and saved to
.Pa $XDG_STATE_HOME/music/playlist.txt ,
or
.Pa ~/.local/state/music/playlist.txt
when
.Ev XDG_STATE_HOME
is unset.
.Sh COMMANDS
Clients send one newline-terminated command per connection.
The public client commands are normally sent with
.Xr sc 1
and
.Xr sq 1 .
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width clearall -compact
.It Cm exit
Stop the daemon.
.It Cm list
Write queued song references to the client.
.It Cm status
Write playback state and queue mode to the client.
.It Cm loop
Cycle played songs to the end of the queue.
.It Cm consume
Remove songs after playback.
.It Cm pause
Pause playback.
.It Cm play
Start or resume playback.
.It Cm skip
Skip the current song.
.It Cm stop
Stop playback.
.It Cm toggle
Toggle between playing and paused.
.It Cm clear
Remove queued songs after the active song.
.It Cm clearall
Remove all queued songs and stop playback.
.It Cm queue Ar song
Append a song reference.
.It Cm insert Ar index song
Insert a song reference.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr play 1 ,
.Xr sc 1 ,
.Xr sf 1 ,
.Xr sp 1 ,
.Xr sq 1
